# Cyber Security Portfolio

## Overview
This repository documents my journey into cybersecurity, focusing on building practical skills aligned with real-world security operations.

The goal of this portfolio is to demonstrate hands-on experience, continuous learning, and a strong foundation in cybersecurity concepts relevant to entry-level roles such as:

- SOC Analyst (Level 1)
- Junior Cyber Security Analyst
- IT Support with Security Focus

---

## Objectives
- Build a solid foundation in networking, systems, and cybersecurity
- Develop practical, hands-on experience through labs and projects
- Document investigations and security-related activities
- Prepare for entry-level cybersecurity roles in the UK

---

## Skills Being Developed

### Technical Skills
- Networking fundamentals (TCP/IP, DNS, ports, protocols)
- Windows & Linux systems
- Log analysis (Event Viewer, Linux logs)
- Basic incident investigation
- Security monitoring concepts (SOC)
- Authentication and access control
- Threat detection fundamentals

### Tools & Technologies
- Windows Event Viewer
- Linux (Ubuntu)
- Command Line (Bash / CMD)
- TryHackMe
- Virtual Machines (VirtualBox / VMware)

